title: RuntimeWarning numpy.dtype size changed when running blueoil command
body:
Docker image Version: latest (as-of blueoil/blueoil@sha256:193984edaa307daaa94c66d60d9e5f9b3f0bd944d9a9be5faac23edc5e460e3a )

```
$ docker run --rm -ti blueoil/blueoil:latest --help

/usr/local/pyenv/versions/python3.6/lib/python3.6/importlib/_bootstrap.py:219: RuntimeWarning: numpy.dtype size changed, may indicate binary incompatibility. Expected 96, got 88
  return f(*args, **kwds)
/usr/local/pyenv/versions/python3.6/lib/python3.6/importlib/_bootstrap.py:219: RuntimeWarning: numpy.dtype size changed, may indicate binary incompatibility. Expected 96, got 88
  return f(*args, **kwds)
WARNING:tensorflow:From /usr/local/pyenv/versions/python3.6/lib/python3.6/site-packages/horovod/tensorflow/__init__.py:117: The name tf.global_variables is deprecated. Please use tf.compat.v1.global_variables instead.

WARNING:tensorflow:From /usr/local/pyenv/versions/python3.6/lib/python3.6/site-packages/horovod/tensorflow/__init__.py:143: The name tf.get_default_graph is deprecated. Please use tf.compat.v1.get_default_graph instead.

Usage: blueoil [OPTIONS] COMMAND [ARGS]...

Options:
  --help  Show this message and exit.

Commands:
  convert  Convert trained model to binary files.
  init     Generate blueoil config.
  predict  Predict by using trained model.
  train    Run training.
```
